source: cli/tests/help.rs
expression: text
---
Toolbox for specific rescue operations.

Provide emergency recovery tools for damaged or unrecoverable filesystems. These
operations are potentially dangerous and should only be used when the filesystem
cannot be mounted or accessed through normal means. Most rescue operations
require CAP_SYS_ADMIN and an unmounted filesystem.

Usage: rescue <COMMAND>

Commands:
  chunk-recover          Recover the chunk tree by scanning the device for
                         surviving chunk data
  super-recover          Recover bad superblocks from good copies
  zero-log               Clear the tree log (usable if it's corrupted and
                         prevents mount)
  fix-device-size        Re-align device and super block sizes
  fix-data-checksum      Fix data checksum mismatches
  create-control-device  Create /dev/btrfs-control
  clear-ino-cache        Remove leftover items pertaining to the deprecated
                         inode cache feature
  clear-space-cache      Completely remove the v1 or v2 free space cache
  clear-uuid-tree        Delete uuid tree so that kernel can rebuild it at mount
                         time
  help                   Print this message or the help of the given
                         subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')
